<define-tag description>security update</define-tag>
<define-tag moreinfo>
<p>It was discovered that Konversation, an IRC client for KDE, could be
crashed when receiving malformed messages using FiSH encryption.</p>

<p>For the stable distribution (wheezy), this problem has been fixed in
version 1.4-1+deb7u1.</p>

<p>For the unstable distribution (sid), this problem has been fixed in
version 1.5-2.</p>

<p>We recommend that you upgrade your konversation packages.</p>
</define-tag>

